What is CBRN Training Simulator (Virtual Contamination)?
CBRN Training Simulator (Virtual Contamination) refers to advanced digital systems designed to realistically replicate chemical, biological, radiological, and nuclear (CBRN) exposure scenarios without the use of live hazardous agents. These platforms utilize real-time plume modeling, sensor emulation, interactive contamination mapping, and immersive technologies to create controlled, repeatable training environments for military forces, emergency responders, and civil protection agencies. By providing high-fidelity simulations of contamination spread and response procedures, they significantly enhance operational readiness while eliminating risks associated with traditional live-agent exercises.

